I was told to break up the video content and talk about my goals and my show in LA, so here we go 🙃:

1. Keep making hilarious edits of my daughter. 👶🏽
2. Add better food discipline to my workout discipline. 🥗
3. Perform/Tour because I miss y’all. 🎤
4. Execute the vision God gives me. 🙏🏾

ight bye. ✨

This song almost didn’t happen. Because of Covid, 15 of my sessions for this album were canceled. Only 2 of the producers sent beats to me over email, One of them being the legend @dmile85 . The production on this hit me immediately. The “like I feel” came to me just as soon as I heard the music and I crafted the song around that line. I’m forever grateful to D’Mile and Mereba for lending their talent to this record.

Song: Like I Feel (ft. @mereba)
Album: if You Feel 
Producer: @dmile85 
Mix Engineer: @l10mixedit 
🎥: @413creatives / @designedbyis

Tomorrow we have Dallas based icon @xvromar joining us on the r/audius subreddit for an hour to host an exclusive AmA 🙏

Get to know him more as he discusses all things life & music 🎶

It’s hard to describe the meaning of this song. I wanted to convey this emotion I was feeling but couldn’t name. I’d be asleep and have these amazing dreams but wake back up to the frustrations of my reality. Not quite hopeless but not quite hopeful. I want this song to be there for someone who may feel like this. 💛

Song: A Dream

Project: b l u r r (EP)

Production: @jay 

🎥: @413creatives / @designedbyis

I’m extremely excited to say that on 2/10, I’ll be among the first artists to perform in San Antonio’s brand new venue @stablehallsa at The Pearl! The wonderful @beholdmelat and I are putting on a show for the lovers on VDay Weekend. Head to Stable Hall’s page for the ticket link✨❤️

I’m excited to be partnering with @savethemusic in giving my fans a chance to bid on a 2024 full backstage meet & greet experience for 2, with all proceeds going to the foundation!  So not only will you hang with me, but you’ll be helping a phenomenal cause. 

• For 25 years, Save The Music has been committed to addressing the systemic inequities within music education by ensuring all students have access to the power of making music. 
They offer a full menu of K-12 music education grants that provide multiple access points to discovering and making music at all levels and genres. 

You can bid/give at my link. ALL info is there as well ✨
